==Middle English==

===Noun===
'''starveling'''

# One who is thin from lack of food.

{{rfv}}

===Quotations===
'''1597:''' If I hang, I'll make a fat pair of gallows; for if I hang, old Sir John hangs with me, and thou knowest he is no starveling. &mdash; Shakespeare, Henry IV Part I, II.1

'''1977:''' Our poor little '''starveling''' Tom, who cries all day for victuals, who will see only evil and not good in this world [...] Is it poor little '''starveling''' Jack that must go, or poor little '''starveling''' Will &mdash; What an inquiry of ways and means. &mdash; Thomas Carlyle ''Past and Present'', ISBN 0814705626, p. 10